---
// Layout
import Layout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
// Components
import PreviewTabsList from "../components/previewTabsList.astro";
import Footer from "../components/footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="Adeeb :: Projecs" >
    <main>
        <h1>Projects: “Adeeb أديب” (personal project)</h1>
        <p>It's concerned with Arabic literature. It assumes a business model that enables
        you to order a specific piece of literature to be printed with especial colors
        and font. Then it'll be delivered to the customer, with the ability for the
        customer to follow up the process. And for special customers, it provides them
        with the ability to make bulk orders fast and easy. And if they’re willing to
        signup, they can review all of their past orders.</p>

        <h3>My Role: Frontend & Backend development, it have 2 versions:</h2>
        <ul id="adeeb-overview">
            <li>“Adeeb أديب ” SSR with a REST API 
                ( 
                    <a href="https://adeeb.m-shrief.tech" target="_blank" title="Live demo">Live Deployment</a> - 
                    <a href="https://github.com/M-Shrief/Adeeb_Astro_SSR" target="_blank" title="github repo">Frontend's repo</a> - 
                    <a href="https://github.com/M-Shrief/Adeeb_ExpressTS_Postgres" target="_blank" title="github repo">Backend's repo</a>
                )
                <ul>
                    <li>Tech stack:
                        <ul>
                            <li>TypeScript with HTML & CSS</li>
                            <li>Astro & Vuejs</li>
                            <li>Nodejs & Express.js</li>
                            <li>Postgres & TypeORM with Redis</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Characteristics:
                        <ul>
                            <li>JWT authentication & authorization</li>
                            <li>Data validation with vee-validate & Yup</li>
                            <li>Dark/Light Theme</li>
                            <li>API tests with Mocha & Chai.</li>
                            <li>Using PM2 for process management.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <PreviewTabsList/>
            <li>“Adeeb أديب ” SPA with a REST API 
                ( <a href="https://github.com/M-Shrief/Adeeb_Vue_TS" target="_blank" title="github repo">Frontend's repo</a> - 
                <a href="https://github.com/M-Shrief/Adeeb_ExpressTS" target="_blank" title="github repo">Backend's repo</a> )
                <ul>
                    <li>Tech stack:
                        <ul>
                            <li>TypeScript with HTML & CSS</li>
                            <li>Vuejs with Pinia & vue-router</li>
                            <li>Nodejs & Express.js</li>
                            <li>MongoDB with Redis</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Characteristics:
                        <ul>
                            <li>JWT authentication & authorization</li>
                            <li>Data validation with vee-validate & Yup</li>
                            <li>Dark/Light Theme</li>
                            <li>API tests with Mocha & Chai, frontend component testing with Cypress.</li>
                            <li>Using PM2 for process management.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>        
    </main>
    <Footer/>
</Layout>

<style lang="scss">
main {
    width: 80%;
      margin: 0 auto;

    h1 {
        font-size: 2rem;
    }
    p {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
    }
    #adeeb-overview {
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        ul {
            li {
                margin: 0.3rem auto;
            }
        }
    }

     a {
        text-decoration: none;
        text-decoration: underline; 
        font-weight: 600;
        color: var(--brand);
        opacity: 0.8;
        &:hover {
            opacity: 1;
        }
    }
}
</style>